==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|commitology}} {{qualifier|uncommon}}

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|en|committee|ology}}, introduced by Cyril Northcote Parkinson in humorous essays published in ''The Economist''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˌkɒm.ɪˈtɒl.ə.dʒi/}}
* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|en|/ˌkɑm.ɪˈtɑl.ə.dʒi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|new=1}}

# {{lb|en|European Union}} The system of committees, composed of representatives of the member states, used to oversee European Commission implementing acts made under European Union legislation.
# {{lb|en|humorous}} The [[study]] of how [[committee]]s could work, expand, and ramify.

